&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cardiac Physiologist (ECG/invasive)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Great Ormond Street Hospital for Children NHS Foundation Trust is an internationally renowned centre for the management of children with congenital and acquired heart disease. An opportunity has arisen to join our friendly team in Clinical Physiology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Band 6 Physiologist to perform a range of invasive and non-invasive cardiology investigations including ECG, Holter analysis, cardio-pulmonary exercise testing, working in the interventional cardiac catheter lab and taking an active role within the pacing team. This is an opportunity for a Physiologist to build on their experiences and develop in the challenging world of paediatrics and congenital/inherited heart disease.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emma Carter - Senior Chief Physiologist - emma.carter@gosh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
